    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Presenting a museum-grade 2005 Porsche 911 Carrera S, a superlative example of the 997.1 generation. This vehicle is powered by a naturally aspirated 3.8L flat-six engine, producing 355 horsepower with a linear torque curve delivered through a precise 6-speed Getrag manual transaxle. The mechanical suite includes Porsche Active Suspension Management (PASM) for variable damping and a limited-slip differential for optimal power delivery. The braking system features four-piston aluminum monobloc fixed calipers paired with cross-drilled, internally vented rotors, ensuring zero fade and immediate bite. This chassis has been maintained to an exacting standard, with a documented service history confirming the integrity of the IMS bearing and rear main seal. Finished in pristine condition with no evidence of bore scoring or suspension bushing fatigue, this is a turnkey investment for the discerning purist.",
